=> Record Class (Java)

    -> Record is a special type of class introduced in Java to reduce boilerplate code.

    -> It is mainly used when your class is only storing data.
    
    -> Such classes are called:
            -> Data Carrier Classes
            -> Plain Data Aggregates

    -> Before Record:
            -> We had to manually write:
                    -> fields
                    -> constructor
                    -> getter methods
                    -> equals()
                    -> hashCode()
                    -> toString()

    -> Java developers noticed:
            -> Many classes only store data
            -> But still require lots of repetitive code

    -> So Java introduced:
            -> Record Class
            -> To write clean immutable data classes with very less code

