-> Why Record Fields Are Final?

    -> Record objects are designed to be immutable.

    -> Immutable means:
            -> Object state cannot change after creation

    -> Example (Using Record Class):

            RectangleUsingRecord r = new RectangleUsingRecord(4, 5);

            // Cannot modify later
            // r.length = 10;  <-- This would cause a compilation error

    -> Why Final?
            -> Records use "final" keyword for all fields
            -> Once created, values cannot be changed
            -> This ensures immutability

    -> Benefits:
            -> safety
            -> thread safety
            -> predictability
            -> easier to reason about code

